# Convex Backend Patterns

## Schema Location

All database schema is defined in `convex/schema.ts`. Reference this for table structures.

## Core Tables

```typescript
// Users & Teams
users          // Clerk-synced user data
teams          // Workspaces/organizations
teamMembers    // User-team relationships with roles

// Projects & Widgets
projects       // Feedback collection projects
widgets        // Embeddable widget instances
widgetConfig   // Widget customization

// Feedback
feedback       // Main feedback entries
aiAnalysis     // AI-generated analysis
conversations  // AI chat history
comments       // Team comments
activityLog    // Audit trail

// Integrations
integrations   // Linear, Notion credentials
exports        // Export history
automationRules // Auto-export rules
webhooks       // Webhook configs
webhookLogs    // Delivery tracking

// Settings
apiKeys        // User AI API keys (encrypted)
storageConfig  // External storage credentials
notifications  // User notifications
subscriptions  // Stripe subscription data
```

## Feedback Status Flow

```
new → triaging → drafted → exported → resolved
```

## Query/Mutation Patterns

```typescript
// convex/feedback.ts
import { query, mutation } from "./_generated/server";
import { v } from "convex/values";

export const getFeedback = query({
  args: { projectId: v.id("projects") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Always check auth
    const identity = await ctx.auth.getUserIdentity();
    if (!identity) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
    
    return await ctx.db
      .query("feedback")
      .withIndex("by_project", (q) => q.eq("projectId", args.projectId))
      .order("desc")
      .collect();
  },
});

export const updateFeedbackStatus = mutation({
  args: {
    feedbackId: v.id("feedback"),
    status: v.union(
      v.literal("new"),
      v.literal("triaging"),
      v.literal("drafted"),
      v.literal("exported"),
      v.literal("resolved")
    ),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Auth check, then update
    await ctx.db.patch(args.feedbackId, {
      status: args.status,
      updatedAt: Date.now(),
    });
    
    // Log activity
    await ctx.db.insert("activityLog", {
      feedbackId: args.feedbackId,
      action: "status_changed",
      details: { to: args.status },
      createdAt: Date.now(),
    });
  },
});
```

## Client Usage

```tsx
import { useQuery, useMutation } from "convex/react";
import { api } from "@/convex/_generated/api";

function FeedbackList({ projectId }) {
  const feedback = useQuery(api.feedback.getFeedback, { projectId });
  const updateStatus = useMutation(api.feedback.updateFeedbackStatus);
  
  if (!feedback) return <Loading />;
  
  return (
    <ul>
      {feedback.map((item) => (
        <li key={item._id}>
          {item.title}
          <button onClick={() => updateStatus({ 
            feedbackId: item._id, 
            status: "triaging" 
          })}>
            Start Triage
          </button>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

## Important Rules

1. **Never run automatic migrations** - Create migration files, let user run manually
2. **Warn about schema changes** - If deleting data, explain what and why
3. **Use indexes** - Always query with appropriate index for performance
4. **Real-time by default** - Convex queries auto-update, leverage this
5. **Encrypt sensitive data** - API keys stored encrypted (AES-256)
